topics.title: Array
topics.author: admin
topics.description: An array is a collection of elements stored at contiguous memory locations, allowing efficient indexing.

topics.title: stack
topics.author: admin
topics.description: In computer science, a stack is a fundamental data structure that operates on a last-in, first-out (LIFO) principle.

quize.title: Stack Data Structure Quiz
quize.description: Test your knowledge of stack data structure!

topics.title: queue
topics.author: admin
topics.description: A queue is a FIFO (First In, First Out) data structure where elements are added at the rear and removed from the front.

topics.title: linked list
topics.author: admin
topics.description: A linked list is a linear data structure where elements, called nodes, are connected via pointers. It allows for flexible memory allocation and efficient insertion/deletion operations.

quiz.title: Stack and Linked List Quiz
quiz.description: Test your knowledge of stack and linked list data structures!

topics.title: double linked list
topics.author: admin
topics.description: A doubly linked list is a sequence of elements where each element has pointers to both the next and previous elements, enabling bidirectional traversal.

topics.title: Binary Tree
topics.author: admin
topics.description: A binary tree is a hierarchical structure where each node has at most two children, enabling efficient data storage and retrieval.
